        public static Bounds boundsOf(java.lang.String src,
                              int start,
                              char c,
                              char[] excludePrefixes,
                              char[] excludePostfixes,
                              char[] excludeBinary,
                              boolean[] excludePrefixBackslash,
                              boolean[] excludePostfixBackslash,
                              boolean[] excludeBinaryBackslash,
                              int direction)
        Search for the next occurrence of the given character 'c' in the src String and return the Bounds of the finding.
        Parameters:
        src - The source String to search through.
        start - The start index of the search.
        c - The char to search for.
        excludePrefixes - Prefix chars to exclude from the search. e.g. '('
        excludePostfixes - Postfix chars to exclude from the search. e.g. ')'
        excludeBinary - Binary chars to exclude from the search. e.g. '"'
        excludePrefixBackslash - Prefix chars to escape check before excluding. e.g. '(' and "\(" would be skipped over.
        excludePostfixBackslash - Postfix chars to escape check before excluding. e.g. ')' and "\)" would be skipped over.
        excludeBinaryBackslash - Binary chars to escape check before excluding. e.g. '"' and "\"" would be skipped over.
        direction - The direction to search for the match in.
        Returns:
        The Bounds of the next possible occurrence, if any.
